HEADWORD: Outrance
<hw>Ou`trance"</hw> <pr>(⟦oomac⟧`tr⟦aum⟧Ns")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. See <er>Outr⟦eacute⟧</er>.]</ety> <def>The utmost or last
extremity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Combat a outrance</b></col>, <cd>a fight to the end, or
to the death.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> fight to the finish.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>outrange</ent>⟦br⟧
